cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

The paper is about natural language processing, which is a subfield of computer science that deals with the interaction between computers and human language. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a neural network architecture, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning). The DMN model is trained end-to-end, which suggests the use of optimization algorithms, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions text classification and sequence modeling, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as well.
